HEADWORD: Rectory
<hw>Rec"to*ry</hw> <pr>(-t?*r?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Rectories</plw> <pr>(-r<?/z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>rectorie</ets> or <ets>rectorerie</ets>, LL.
<ets>rectoria</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The province of a rector; a
parish church, parsonage, or spiritual living, with all its rights,
tithes, and glebes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A rector's mansion; a parsonage house.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recto-uterine</ent>⟦br⟧
